records.addlTxt:
9:38 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Prosecuting attorney Shawn N Woller in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant Christopher Cummings in court, in custody at WCJ.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court for Christopher Cummings.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and confirms with counsel parties are prepared to proceed today.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Griffis confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty. 

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Griffis.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

6 Months Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS (25 Days Credit IF revoked - Court will allow transfer to the County in which the defendant resides).

Term of Probation: 12 Months (Court will allow transfer to the County in which the defendant resides)

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact with any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;
-	Make best efforts to Maintain/Obtain full time employment, schooling or a combination of the two.

COSTS:  $268.00;

DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
